Numpy, Pandas, and Matplotlib are not relevant for a MERN-focused role (they are for Data Science).

Change the structure 
Languages: JavaScript (ES6+), Python  
Frontend: HTML5, CSS3, React.js, Redux Toolkit  
Backend: Node.js, Express.js, REST APIs  
Database: MongoDB, MySQL  
Tools: Git, GitHub, NPM, NPX  

Show latest career first : show full stack career on top

Remover everything that is not related to MERN stack 

Objective be like: Aspiring full-stack web developer with hands-on experience in MERN stack, seeking to contribute to innovative product development and grow within a dynamic tech team.

No links (GitHub/Live URLs)?

Certificates – Poorly Organized
	•	Dates are random.
	•	Mentioning platforms (like Udemy, Great Learning) is okay but don’t overdo it.

Make it uniform, e.g.:
	•	Full Stack Web Development, Ensono Research Pvt Ltd — Mar 2024
	•	React Developer, Udemy — May 2023

Add a GitHub and LinkedIn URL as clickable links (if in PDF).
	•	Avoid “Jspiders” logo or institute names unless they are well-known.
	•	Prefer “Professional Summary” over “Career Objective” in modern resumes.
	•	Stick to 1-page unless you have 4+ years of experience.

Rewrite career objective to be personal and impactful.
	2.	Organize skills properly and remove irrelevant ones.
	3.	Improve project descriptions with links and outcomes.
	4.	Redesign resume layout using a clean, professional template.
	5.	Make certifications and achievements more concrete and readable.





<View style={styles.blueSectionArea}>
          {/* NEW THIS WEEK */}
          <View style={styles.sectionWrapper}>
            <View style={styles.arrowBox}>
              {arrow.week.left && (
                <TouchableOpacity
                  style={styles.arrowSingle}
                  onPress={() => slideLeft(refWeek)}
                >
                  <Text style={styles.arrowText}>{"<"}</Text>
                </TouchableOpacity>
              )}
              {arrow.week.right && (
                <TouchableOpacity
                  style={styles.arrowSingle}
                  onPress={() => slideRight(refWeek)}
                >
                  <Text style={styles.arrowText}>{">"}</Text>
                </TouchableOpacity>
              )}
            </View>

            <Text style={styles.sectionTitle}>New This Week</Text>

            <ScrollView
              ref={refWeek}
              horizontal
              onScroll={(e) => handleScroll(e, "week", refWeek)}
              showsHorizontalScrollIndicator={false}
              contentContainerStyle={styles.sectionRow}
            >
             
             {newWeek_arrayData.map((item, index) => (
  <GradientImageGridImage
    key={`week-${item.id || index}`}
    uniqueKey={`week-${index}`}
    activeCardIndex={activeCardIndex}
    setActiveCardIndex={setActiveCardIndex}
    videoUrl={item.videoUrl}
    thumbnail={item.thumbnail}
    title={item.title}
    description={item.description}
  />
))}


            </ScrollView>
          </View>


